pageContext.claim: “I'm paying a normalized interest rate. We should be paying less, frankly. This guy has made a big mistake. He's made a big mistake -- the head of the Fed. That was another beauty that I chose. But even with that, we're paying a normalized interest rate. The nice thing is you get some interest from the bank. With President Obama, he was paying nothing. It's easy to make money when you you're paying nothing; you're paying zero.”
pageContext.analysis: Obama, of course, faced the worst economic crisis since the Great Depression, with unemployment reaching 10 percent. The economy is now basically at full employment. Zero percent interest rates would mean the economy was again in a free fall — presumably not something Trump wants.
